<section id="Logo">
  <title>PLD Logo</title>
  <para>
    The idea of our logo was born in Agnieszka Slota`s head.
  </para>
  <para>
    The graphics was later designed by Marcin Mierzejewski (Kevin) 
    and made using paintbrush and Indian ink by Maciek Zielinski.
  </para>
  
  <section id="big-logo">
    <title>Big logos</title>
    <para>
      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
	  <para>
            This logo may only be used if: 
             <itemizedlist>
               <listitem>
	         <para>
	           the product it is used for is made using a documented 
	           procedure as published on www.pld-linux.org (for example 
	           official CD-creation)
	         </para>
	       </listitem>
	       <listitem>
	         <para>
                   official approval is given by PLD Linux for its use in 
   	    	   this purpose 
		 </para>
	       </listitem>
             </itemizedlist>
	   </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
	  <para>
	    May be used if an official part of PLD (decided using the 
	    rules in I) is part of the complete product, if it is made 
	    clear that only this part is officially approved
	  </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
	  <para>
	    We reserve the right to revoke a license for a product 
	  </para>
        </listitem>
      </orderedlist>
      Permission has been given to use the official logo on clothing 
      (shirts, hats, etc) as long as they are made by a PLD developer and 
      not sold for profit.
    </para>
    <para>
      Disclaimer: License stolen from Debian.
    </para>
    <figure>
      <title>The main logo</title>
      <mediaobject>
	<imageobject>
	  <imagedata
		  fileref="figures/pld_pure.png"
		     format="PNG"/>
	</imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    
    <figure>
